{"id":"lustre-lustre-parallel-file-system-for-ai-a-e17c5421510539f2","source_id":"lustre","title":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","url":"/resources/lustre","section_path":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","doc_family":"infrastructure","doc_type":"markdown","product_tags":["lustre","parallel-file-system","storage","throughput","ost","mds"],"updated_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","retrieved_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","content_hash":"e17c5421510539f2","doc_version":null,"snapshot_id":"20260315","source_kind":"corpus","content":"Lustre is the most widely deployed parallel file system in high-performance computing, powering the majority of Top500 supercomputers and the largest AI training clusters. It scales to exabyte capacities and terabytes-per-second aggregate bandwidth, with separated metadata and data paths enabling massive parallelism for I/O-intensive distributed GPU training.","sparse_terms":["lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","lustre","is","the","most","widely","deployed","parallel","file","system","in","high-performance","computing","powering","the","majority","of","top500","supercomputers","and","the","largest","ai","training","clusters.","it","scales","to","exabyte","capacities","and","terabytes-per-second","aggregate","bandwidth","with","separated","metadata","and","data","paths","enabling","massive","parallelism","for","i/o-intensive","distributed","gpu","training."],"metadata":{}}
{"id":"lustre-architecture-43b09ca2316e2078","source_id":"lustre","title":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","url":"/resources/lustre","section_path":"Architecture","doc_family":"infrastructure","doc_type":"markdown","product_tags":["lustre","parallel-file-system","storage","throughput","ost","mds"],"updated_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","retrieved_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","content_hash":"43b09ca2316e2078","doc_version":null,"snapshot_id":"20260315","source_kind":"corpus","content":"Lustre uses a client-server architecture with distinct roles: - **MGS (Management Server)** — stores cluster-wide configuration. Clients contact the MGS at mount time to discover filesystem topology. Typically colocated with the primary MDS. - **MDS / MDT (Metadata Server / Target)** — handles namespace operations: create, open, stat, unlink, readdir. The MDT is typically an NVMe-backed ZFS or ldiskfs volume. - **OSS / OST (Object Storage Server / Target)** — stores file data as objects. Each OSS manages multiple OSTs. File data is striped across OSTs for parallel access. - **Clients** — mount via the kernel module (`lustre.ko`), communicating directly with MDSes for metadata and OSSes for data.","sparse_terms":["lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","architecture","lustre","uses","a","client-server","architecture","with","distinct","roles","mgs","management","server","stores","cluster-wide","configuration.","clients","contact","the","mgs","at","mount","time","to","discover","filesystem","topology.","typically","colocated","with","the","primary","mds.","mds","mdt","metadata","server","target","handles","namespace","operations","create","open","stat","unlink","readdir.","the","mdt","is","typically","an","nvme-backed","zfs","or","ldiskfs","volume.","oss","ost","object","storage","server","target","stores","file","data","as","objects.","each","oss","manages","multiple","osts.","file","data","is","striped","across","osts","for","parallel","access.","clients","mount","via","the","kernel","module","lustre.ko","communicating","directly","with","mdses","for","metadata","and","osses","for","data."],"metadata":{}}
{"id":"lustre-striping-configuration-419417168f13ed1b","source_id":"lustre","title":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","url":"/resources/lustre","section_path":"Striping Configuration","doc_family":"infrastructure","doc_type":"markdown","product_tags":["lustre","parallel-file-system","storage","throughput","ost","mds"],"updated_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","retrieved_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","content_hash":"419417168f13ed1b","doc_version":null,"snapshot_id":"20260315","source_kind":"corpus","content":"Lustre stripes files across OSTs using `lfs setstripe`: ```bash lfs setstripe -c 8 -S 4M /mnt/lustre/training-data lfs getstripe /mnt/lustre/training-data/dataset.tar ``` - **Stripe count (`-c`)** — number of OSTs per file. `-c -1` stripes across all OSTs for maximum bandwidth. - **Stripe size (`-S`)** — contiguous bytes per OST before rotating. Default 1 MB; use 4-16 MB for checkpoints to reduce lock contention. **Progressive File Layout (PFL)** dynamically adjusts striping as files grow: ```bash lfs setstripe -E 64K -c 1 -S 64K -E 1G -c 4 -S 1M -E -1 -c -1 -S 4M /mnt/lustre/mixed ```","sparse_terms":["lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","striping","configuration","lustre","stripes","files","across","osts","using","lfs","setstripe","bash","lfs","setstripe","c","8","s","4m","mnt/lustre/training-data","lfs","getstripe","mnt/lustre/training-data/dataset.tar","stripe","count","c","number","of","osts","per","file.","c","1","stripes","across","all","osts","for","maximum","bandwidth.","stripe","size","s","contiguous","bytes","per","ost","before","rotating.","default","1","mb","use","4-16","mb","for","checkpoints","to","reduce","lock","contention.","progressive","file","layout","pfl","dynamically","adjusts","striping","as","files","grow","bash","lfs","setstripe","e","64k","c","1","s","64k","e","1g","c","4","s","1m","e","1","c","1","s","4m","mnt/lustre/mixed"],"metadata":{}}
{"id":"lustre-dne-distributed-namespace-62396a22d2416274","source_id":"lustre","title":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","url":"/resources/lustre","section_path":"DNE (Distributed Namespace)","doc_family":"infrastructure","doc_type":"markdown","product_tags":["lustre","parallel-file-system","storage","throughput","ost","mds"],"updated_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","retrieved_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","content_hash":"62396a22d2416274","doc_version":null,"snapshot_id":"20260315","source_kind":"corpus","content":"DNE spreads metadata across multiple MDTs. DNE1 assigns subdirectories to specific MDTs (`lfs mkdir -i <index>`). DNE2 hash-distributes a single directory's entries across MDTs (`lfs mkdir -c 4 /mnt/lustre/high-iops-dir`), parallelizing readdir, create, and stat for directories with millions of files. Essential for ImageNet-scale datasets.","sparse_terms":["lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","dne","distributed","namespace","dne","spreads","metadata","across","multiple","mdts.","dne1","assigns","subdirectories","to","specific","mdts","lfs","mkdir","i","index","dne2","hash-distributes","a","single","directory","s","entries","across","mdts","lfs","mkdir","c","4","mnt/lustre/high-iops-dir","parallelizing","readdir","create","and","stat","for","directories","with","millions","of","files.","essential","for","imagenet-scale","datasets."],"metadata":{}}
{"id":"lustre-file-locking-ldlm-be9aac0292c544b9","source_id":"lustre","title":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","url":"/resources/lustre","section_path":"File Locking (LDLM)","doc_family":"infrastructure","doc_type":"markdown","product_tags":["lustre","parallel-file-system","storage","throughput","ost","mds"],"updated_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","retrieved_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","content_hash":"be9aac0292c544b9","doc_version":null,"snapshot_id":"20260315","source_kind":"corpus","content":"Lustre's Distributed Lock Manager coordinates concurrent access via extent locks and inode locks. AI workload contention patterns include checkpoint storms (mitigate with per-rank directories or `lfs mkdir -c`) and shared-file stat contention (tune with `lctl set_param llite.*.statahead_max=128`).","sparse_terms":["lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","file","locking","ldlm","lustre","s","distributed","lock","manager","coordinates","concurrent","access","via","extent","locks","and","inode","locks.","ai","workload","contention","patterns","include","checkpoint","storms","mitigate","with","per-rank","directories","or","lfs","mkdir","c","and","shared-file","stat","contention","tune","with","lctl","set_param","llite.","statahead_max","128"],"metadata":{}}
{"id":"lustre-performance-tuning-5c24195f814a8d3f","source_id":"lustre","title":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","url":"/resources/lustre","section_path":"Performance Tuning","doc_family":"infrastructure","doc_type":"markdown","product_tags":["lustre","parallel-file-system","storage","throughput","ost","mds"],"updated_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","retrieved_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","content_hash":"5c24195f814a8d3f","doc_version":null,"snapshot_id":"20260315","source_kind":"corpus","content":"Critical parameters for AI workloads: - **RPC size** — `lctl set_param osc.*.max_pages_per_rpc=4096` (16 MB with 4K pages) - **OST threads** — `lctl set_param ost.OSS.ost_io.threads_max=512` - **Read-ahead** — `lctl set_param llite.*.max_read_ahead_mb=256` for sequential loading - **Stripe alignment** — align I/O to stripe boundaries; PyTorch DataLoader buffers should be multiples of stripe size - **Client cache** — `lctl set_param llite.*.max_cached_mb=2048`; increase for re-read workloads, reduce for streaming","sparse_terms":["lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","performance","tuning","critical","parameters","for","ai","workloads","rpc","size","lctl","set_param","osc.","max_pages_per_rpc","4096","16","mb","with","4k","pages","ost","threads","lctl","set_param","ost.oss.ost_io.threads_max","512","read-ahead","lctl","set_param","llite.","max_read_ahead_mb","256","for","sequential","loading","stripe","alignment","align","i/o","to","stripe","boundaries","pytorch","dataloader","buffers","should","be","multiples","of","stripe","size","client","cache","lctl","set_param","llite.","max_cached_mb","2048","increase","for","re-read","workloads","reduce","for","streaming"],"metadata":{}}
{"id":"lustre-lustre-and-gpudirect-storage-765c161edbb63920","source_id":"lustre","title":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","url":"/resources/lustre","section_path":"Lustre and GPUDirect Storage","doc_family":"infrastructure","doc_type":"markdown","product_tags":["lustre","parallel-file-system","storage","throughput","ost","mds"],"updated_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","retrieved_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","content_hash":"765c161edbb63920","doc_version":null,"snapshot_id":"20260315","source_kind":"corpus","content":"GPUDirect Storage enables direct transfers between OSTs and GPU memory, bypassing CPU page cache and DMA bounce buffers. Reduces checkpoint latency by up to 3x. Requires `nvidia-fs` kernel module, Lustre 2.15+ with GDS patches, and the `cuFile` API (DALI, KvikIO, Magnum IO).","sparse_terms":["lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","lustre","and","gpudirect","storage","gpudirect","storage","enables","direct","transfers","between","osts","and","gpu","memory","bypassing","cpu","page","cache","and","dma","bounce","buffers.","reduces","checkpoint","latency","by","up","to","3x.","requires","nvidia-fs","kernel","module","lustre","2.15+","with","gds","patches","and","the","cufile","api","dali","kvikio","magnum","io"],"metadata":{}}
{"id":"lustre-checkpoint-i-o-patterns-181f188d726fc2d3","source_id":"lustre","title":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","url":"/resources/lustre","section_path":"Checkpoint I/O Patterns","doc_family":"infrastructure","doc_type":"markdown","product_tags":["lustre","parallel-file-system","storage","throughput","ost","mds"],"updated_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","retrieved_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","content_hash":"181f188d726fc2d3","doc_version":null,"snapshot_id":"20260315","source_kind":"corpus","content":"A 175B parameter model produces ~350 GB per checkpoint. Lustre strategies: stripe across all OSTs (`-c -1 -S 8M`), stagger write timing across ranks, use `O_DIRECT` to bypass page cache, write per-rank shard files to avoid lock contention, and overlap checkpoint I/O with training via asynchronous writes.","sparse_terms":["lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","checkpoint","i/o","patterns","a","175b","parameter","model","produces","350","gb","per","checkpoint.","lustre","strategies","stripe","across","all","osts","c","1","s","8m","stagger","write","timing","across","ranks","use","o_direct","to","bypass","page","cache","write","per-rank","shard","files","to","avoid","lock","contention","and","overlap","checkpoint","i/o","with","training","via","asynchronous","writes."],"metadata":{}}
{"id":"lustre-data-loading-challenges-e582e543dd24b536","source_id":"lustre","title":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","url":"/resources/lustre","section_path":"Data Loading Challenges","doc_family":"infrastructure","doc_type":"markdown","product_tags":["lustre","parallel-file-system","storage","throughput","ost","mds"],"updated_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","retrieved_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","content_hash":"e582e543dd24b536","doc_version":null,"snapshot_id":"20260315","source_kind":"corpus","content":"Small-file random reads stress metadata. Mitigations: tar-based datasets (WebDataset, FFCV, TFRecord) converting millions of reads into sequential I/O, DNE2 striped directories for high-file-count directories, and local NVMe caching to read from Lustre only once per epoch.","sparse_terms":["lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","data","loading","challenges","small-file","random","reads","stress","metadata.","mitigations","tar-based","datasets","webdataset","ffcv","tfrecord","converting","millions","of","reads","into","sequential","i/o","dne2","striped","directories","for","high-file-count","directories","and","local","nvme","caching","to","read","from","lustre","only","once","per","epoch."],"metadata":{}}
{"id":"lustre-hsm-hierarchical-storage-management-0ec6257cf327184a","source_id":"lustre","title":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","url":"/resources/lustre","section_path":"HSM (Hierarchical Storage Management)","doc_family":"infrastructure","doc_type":"markdown","product_tags":["lustre","parallel-file-system","storage","throughput","ost","mds"],"updated_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","retrieved_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","content_hash":"0ec6257cf327184a","doc_version":null,"snapshot_id":"20260315","source_kind":"corpus","content":"Lustre HSM tiers data to external storage (tape, object, cloud). Archived files leave stubs on Lustre; access triggers transparent restore. Useful for retaining old checkpoints without consuming NVMe capacity. Managed via `lhsmtool_posix` or `lhsmtool_s3` copytool agents.","sparse_terms":["lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","hsm","hierarchical","storage","management","lustre","hsm","tiers","data","to","external","storage","tape","object","cloud","archived","files","leave","stubs","on","lustre","access","triggers","transparent","restore.","useful","for","retaining","old","checkpoints","without","consuming","nvme","capacity.","managed","via","lhsmtool_posix","or","lhsmtool_s3","copytool","agents."],"metadata":{}}
{"id":"lustre-monitoring-59612c8566d3ed23","source_id":"lustre","title":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","url":"/resources/lustre","section_path":"Monitoring","doc_family":"infrastructure","doc_type":"markdown","product_tags":["lustre","parallel-file-system","storage","throughput","ost","mds"],"updated_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","retrieved_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","content_hash":"59612c8566d3ed23","doc_version":null,"snapshot_id":"20260315","source_kind":"corpus","content":"- **`lctl get_param`** — runtime parameters and statistics (`osc.*.stats`, `llite.*.stats`) - **Lustre Jobstats** — per-job I/O accounting: `lctl set_param jobid_var=procname_uid` - **`lfs df`** — per-OST and per-MDT space usage - **Health checks** — `lctl get_param health_check` on clients and servers","sparse_terms":["lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","monitoring","lctl","get_param","runtime","parameters","and","statistics","osc.","stats","llite.","stats","lustre","jobstats","per-job","i/o","accounting","lctl","set_param","jobid_var","procname_uid","lfs","df","per-ost","and","per-mdt","space","usage","health","checks","lctl","get_param","health_check","on","clients","and","servers"],"metadata":{}}
{"id":"lustre-scale-and-deployments-95767c222939a317","source_id":"lustre","title":"Lustre Parallel File System for AI and HPC Storage","url":"/resources/lustre","section_path":"Scale and Deployments","doc_family":"infrastructure","doc_type":"markdown","product_tags":["lustre","parallel-file-system","storage","throughput","ost","mds"],"updated_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","retrieved_at":"2026-03-15T13:52:27.202946+00:00","content_hash":"95767c222939a317","doc_version":null,"snapshot_id":"20260315","source_kind":"corpus","content":"The largest deployments exceed 1 exabyte and 1 TB/s aggregate bandwidth (Frontier, El Capitan). Commercial appliances from DDN (EXAScaler), HPE (ClusterStor), and NetApp provide integrated hardware, distribution, and support. DDN AI400X appliances deliver 90 GB/s per unit with NVMe-backed OSTs and GPUDirect Storage support.","sparse_terms":["lustre","parallel","file","system","for","ai","and","hpc","storage","scale","and","deployments","the","largest","deployments","exceed","1","exabyte","and","1","tb/s","aggregate","bandwidth","frontier","el","capitan","commercial","appliances","from","ddn","exascaler","hpe","clusterstor","and","netapp","provide","integrated","hardware","distribution","and","support.","ddn","ai400x","appliances","deliver","90","gb/s","per","unit","with","nvme-backed","osts","and","gpudirect","storage","support."],"metadata":{}}